## What Makes This Publishable & Novel

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Most traffic datasets are static snapshots. This dataset is **temporally continuous** (every 60s), **multi-modal** (traffic + weather + taxi + air quality), and **annotated with operational metadata** (camera reliability, weather conditions). That combination doesn't exist on Kaggle today.

**Kaggle dataset name:** `Singapore Smart City Traffic — Multi-Modal Temporal Dataset`

**Unique selling points:**
1. **Temporal continuity** — not random snapshots, but continuous surveillance-style data
2. **Multi-modal enrichment** — every image tagged with weather, taxi density, air quality
3. **Failure annotations** — each frame has a quality/reliability label
4. **Drift baselines** — published baseline drift metrics for benchmarking

